WEBVTT

01:27.160 --> 01:35.020
[LIVE UP TO YOUR YOUTH]

01:35.509 --> 01:37.800
[Episode 4]

01:38.950 --> 01:39.600
Come on.

01:39.660 --> 01:41.210
Look. I braised these myself.

01:41.210 --> 01:43.140
-You're being too kind.
-Go ahead.

01:43.259 --> 01:44.920
That's really too kind of you.

01:44.950 --> 01:45.500
It's my pleasure.

01:45.500 --> 01:46.450
Go ahead and try it.

01:46.450 --> 01:47.450
Thank you so much.

01:47.680 --> 01:48.340
Here. Try some.

01:48.340 --> 01:49.009
-Duck tongue.
-It's okay—

01:49.009 --> 01:49.850
You know the motto

01:49.850 --> 01:50.910
of Wenzhou people?

01:50.920 --> 01:52.009
"No matter how poor,
never work for others.

01:52.009 --> 01:52.950
No matter how hungry, never beg for food.

01:52.950 --> 01:53.979
We'd rather sleep on the floor

01:53.979 --> 01:55.380
than not be our own boss."

01:55.450 --> 01:56.140
You're young,

01:56.140 --> 01:57.789
always busy and never tired.

01:58.060 --> 01:59.590
You'll definitely make it.

01:59.789 --> 02:00.840
What you just said,

02:00.840 --> 02:02.010
could you say that again?

02:02.010 --> 02:03.090
Why would you want to write that down?

02:03.090 --> 02:04.120
I am a screenwriter.

02:04.120 --> 02:05.200
When I hear something interesting,

02:05.200 --> 02:06.060
I write it down.

02:06.060 --> 02:06.760
Really? A screenwriter?

02:06.760 --> 02:07.370
He's a screenwriter.

02:07.370 --> 02:08.580
I'm studying to become a singer.

02:08.580 --> 02:09.520
We just arrived in Beijing.

02:09.520 --> 02:10.960
We're setting up a stall
to make ends meet.

02:10.960 --> 02:12.560
We're in it for the long haul.

02:13.300 --> 02:15.310
Not asking your family for money.
That's great.

02:15.310 --> 02:16.170
Such good kids.

02:16.840 --> 02:17.240
I really should

02:17.240 --> 02:18.910
give you some proper advice then.

02:18.910 --> 02:19.650
We Wenzhou people

02:19.650 --> 02:20.970
have our own formula for doing business.

02:20.970 --> 02:22.360
The way you're displaying things now

02:22.360 --> 02:23.340
isn't quite right.

02:23.340 --> 02:24.200
Let me show you.

02:25.910 --> 02:27.100
"If you display it,

02:27.190 --> 02:28.120
people will buy it."

02:28.120 --> 02:29.400
You should have them high.

02:29.400 --> 02:29.870
Right?

02:30.000 --> 02:31.170
"If you display a lot,

02:31.170 --> 02:32.500
people will check them out.

02:32.500 --> 02:33.680
If the goods are neat,

02:33.680 --> 02:34.750
the customers will be pleased.

02:34.750 --> 02:35.960
If the quality is good,

02:35.960 --> 02:37.400
the business will last till you're old."

02:37.400 --> 02:37.800
Right?

02:37.800 --> 02:38.280
Makes sense.

02:38.280 --> 02:38.930
These here

02:38.930 --> 02:39.840
aren't enough.

02:39.900 --> 02:40.780
Not enough to choose from.

02:40.780 --> 02:41.470
Come on, have them out.

02:41.470 --> 02:42.340
Put them here.

02:42.430 --> 02:42.910
Okay.

02:43.460 --> 02:43.860
Right.

02:44.620 --> 02:45.840
Don't make it too crowded though.

02:45.840 --> 02:47.370
It'll make them look cheap.

02:47.750 --> 02:48.700
Look at this one.

02:48.910 --> 02:49.590
This is a great brand,

02:49.590 --> 02:51.050
you shouldn't put it here.

02:51.130 --> 02:52.210
Nobody will see it.

02:52.310 --> 02:52.840
Let's hang it up.

02:52.840 --> 02:53.750
Yes, hang it up.

02:55.500 --> 02:56.000
Exactly.

02:56.000 --> 02:57.360
What did I just say?

02:57.530 --> 02:58.360
"If you display it,

02:58.360 --> 02:58.930
people will buy it."

02:58.930 --> 02:59.590
And?

02:59.690 --> 03:00.890
"If you display a lot,

03:00.900 --> 03:02.030
people will check them out."

03:02.030 --> 03:02.430
Right.

03:03.240 --> 03:04.870
Here, let me put this up for you.

03:04.870 --> 03:05.410
And also,

03:05.430 --> 03:06.890
the most important thing—

03:06.960 --> 03:08.360
you need to hawk your wares.

03:08.360 --> 03:09.870
Which of you two can do that?

03:09.870 --> 03:10.180
You?

03:10.590 --> 03:11.860
I... I'll do it.

03:11.930 --> 03:12.250
Yeah?

03:12.250 --> 03:13.360
Alright, here we go.

03:13.360 --> 03:14.480
Arm up, hand on hip.

03:15.430 --> 03:17.290
Check this out! Don't miss out!

03:17.360 --> 03:18.579
Louder! Louder!

03:18.680 --> 03:20.020
Check this out!

03:20.250 --> 03:21.410
Don't miss out!

03:21.470 --> 03:22.960
Head up, chest out. Confidence!

03:22.960 --> 03:23.690
Confidence!

03:23.910 --> 03:24.510
That's it!

03:24.520 --> 03:26.210
Check this out! Don't miss out!

03:26.210 --> 03:26.970
Come and take a look!

03:26.970 --> 03:27.410
Good.

03:27.520 --> 03:28.300
How much?

03:28.370 --> 03:29.579
Twenty yuan per piece.

03:29.579 --> 03:30.370
Twenty.

03:30.430 --> 03:31.700
Twenty per piece!

03:31.900 --> 03:34.090
Check this out! Don't miss out!

03:34.400 --> 03:34.960
Very promising.

03:34.960 --> 03:36.360
You won't get ripped off!

03:36.590 --> 03:37.590
Thank you so much.

03:38.090 --> 03:39.970
We're both from Wenzhou—you're so welcome.

03:39.970 --> 03:41.220
Twenty. It's a bargain.

03:41.220 --> 03:42.650
This is from Guangzhou.

03:42.780 --> 03:43.800
A silk blend.

03:44.370 --> 03:45.930
Great quality. Wrinkle-free.

03:45.930 --> 03:46.930
-Here comes business.
-You can try it on.

03:46.930 --> 03:47.780
Feel free to try it on.

03:47.780 --> 03:48.710
This looks really nice.

03:48.710 --> 03:49.310
Yes!

03:49.310 --> 03:50.620
This one is 20 yuan.

03:50.740 --> 03:52.730
Check this out! Don't miss out!

03:53.520 --> 03:54.720
You won't regret it!

03:54.840 --> 03:56.240
You won't get ripped off!

04:03.080 --> 04:04.310
Why are you cleaning it here?

04:04.310 --> 04:05.310
You can't clean it here.

04:05.310 --> 04:05.900
Leave.

04:05.930 --> 04:06.590
Okay.

04:08.190 --> 04:09.520
I'm in the way, aren't I?

04:11.360 --> 04:13.150
Why are you still sitting there? Move!

04:13.150 --> 04:13.670
Move it!

04:13.740 --> 04:14.660
I am, I am.

04:14.750 --> 04:15.830
I am moving.

04:17.300 --> 04:19.190
Do you need your range hood cleaned?

04:19.190 --> 04:20.240
No, I don't.

04:20.890 --> 04:21.570
Go clean it outside.

04:21.570 --> 04:22.370
Okay.

04:22.500 --> 04:24.230
You're blocking the entrance.

04:31.980 --> 04:32.750
Thank you.

04:33.320 --> 04:34.450
How much is this one?

04:35.510 --> 04:36.180
This one?

04:36.480 --> 04:37.810
It's our first day of business today—

04:37.810 --> 04:39.220
what about 45?

04:39.330 --> 04:40.270
Okay, 45.

04:40.330 --> 04:40.690
Okay.

04:41.750 --> 04:42.770
Does it fit well?

04:42.830 --> 04:43.830
It fits perfectly.

04:43.830 --> 04:45.360
Let me tighten this for you.

04:45.560 --> 04:45.920
Okay.

04:46.190 --> 04:47.050
Take the money.

04:47.250 --> 04:47.800
Here.

04:48.430 --> 04:48.830
Thank you.

04:48.830 --> 04:49.930
Please pack this one up for us.

04:49.930 --> 04:50.300
Okay.

04:50.300 --> 04:51.630
-Okay. Thank you.
-Just a second.

04:51.630 --> 04:52.190
I'll put it here.

04:52.190 --> 04:53.050
Very nice.

04:53.120 --> 04:53.970
Okay.

04:54.120 --> 04:55.470
It really suits you.

04:55.740 --> 04:56.340
Thank you.

04:58.060 --> 04:58.430
Here.

04:58.870 --> 04:59.200
Here.

05:02.450 --> 05:02.940
Here.

05:03.360 --> 05:04.040
Thank you.

05:04.050 --> 05:05.060
Here, I'll take it.

05:05.060 --> 05:05.510
Would you like

05:05.510 --> 05:06.630
a denim shirt for yourself?

05:06.630 --> 05:07.010
Yeah.

05:07.010 --> 05:08.270
Not enough money left.

05:08.430 --> 05:08.860
Okay.

05:09.300 --> 05:09.930
Next time then.

05:09.930 --> 05:10.360
Next time.

05:10.360 --> 05:10.950
-Okay.
-Next time.

05:10.950 --> 05:12.590
Tell your friends about us.

05:12.680 --> 05:13.140
Will do.

05:20.220 --> 05:21.560
Twenty, thirty, forty—

05:21.630 --> 05:22.690
I'll be right back.

05:25.560 --> 05:26.160
Five.

05:33.060 --> 05:33.540
My hero.

05:34.130 --> 05:34.930
Thanks, boss.

05:37.659 --> 05:38.720
So, starting today,

05:38.720 --> 05:40.040
our little stall

05:40.180 --> 05:41.950
is officially up and running.

05:43.630 --> 05:46.230
Partner, looking forward
to working with you.

05:47.000 --> 05:47.620
Me too.

05:52.850 --> 05:54.780
But let's get this straight first.

05:54.890 --> 05:56.450
I have classes from Monday to Friday.

05:56.450 --> 05:57.580
I can only come on weekends.

05:57.580 --> 05:59.940
If I hear from the film studio,
I have to go too.

05:59.940 --> 06:01.450
But I'll ask for leave in advance.

06:01.450 --> 06:02.110
No problem.

06:02.950 --> 06:03.930
Mr. Zheng said

06:03.930 --> 06:05.250
I need to take care of my voice.

06:05.250 --> 06:06.950
I'll handle styling and sales,

06:06.950 --> 06:08.160
and you do the hawking.

06:08.160 --> 06:09.300
Sure thing.

06:09.480 --> 06:10.310
But while I do that,

06:10.310 --> 06:11.190
I might also jot down notes

06:11.190 --> 06:12.450
about life from time to time.

06:12.450 --> 06:13.440
No problem.

06:13.480 --> 06:15.140
Just say you're bookkeeping.

06:15.190 --> 06:17.510
We'll closely work together
to negotiate a good price.

06:17.510 --> 06:18.910
How do we split the money?

06:20.270 --> 06:21.530
Five hundred in total;

06:21.570 --> 06:22.970
400 from me, 100 from you.

06:23.090 --> 06:24.290
Let's split it 20-80.

06:24.310 --> 06:25.570
Who gets 20 and who gets 80?

06:25.570 --> 06:27.070
I get 80 and you get 20, obviously.

06:27.070 --> 06:27.870
That won't do.

06:27.930 --> 06:28.660
No?

06:28.860 --> 06:30.070
I should get less.

06:30.160 --> 06:31.870
I borrowed my 100 from you.

06:33.770 --> 06:35.620
If I wanted more, I'd be doing it alone.

06:35.620 --> 06:37.280
I won't take advantage of you.

06:37.630 --> 06:38.360
That 100 yuan,

06:38.360 --> 06:39.760
you can pay me back later.

06:39.860 --> 06:40.630
Let's keep things separate.

06:40.630 --> 06:41.890
Business is business.

06:42.560 --> 06:44.360
As befits someone from Wenzhou—

06:44.950 --> 06:45.680
very shrewd.

07:31.770 --> 07:32.260
Song?

07:33.070 --> 07:33.570
Song?

07:34.250 --> 07:35.310
Song, Little Song?

07:35.810 --> 07:36.540
Little Song?

07:37.159 --> 07:37.890
Little Song?

07:38.190 --> 07:38.920
Little Song,

07:39.250 --> 07:39.980
my child.

07:40.300 --> 07:42.040
-Keep it down, we're sleeping.
-Keep it down.

07:42.040 --> 07:43.390
What are you doing this early?

07:43.390 --> 07:43.950
Zongbao,

07:44.180 --> 07:45.040
Little Song...

07:45.430 --> 07:46.740
My son, Little Song, is missing.

07:46.740 --> 07:47.670
I can't find him.

07:47.770 --> 07:49.230
Good riddance. He stank.

07:49.420 --> 07:50.360
What are you saying?

07:50.360 --> 07:51.560
Did you get rid of him?

07:51.950 --> 07:53.060
I don't have time for that.

07:53.060 --> 07:54.120
Keep looking.

07:54.270 --> 07:54.750
Little Song?

07:54.750 --> 07:55.450
I did.

07:55.450 --> 07:56.300
I've looked

07:56.540 --> 07:58.400
literally everywhere, Zongbao.

07:58.500 --> 07:59.700
-Little Song?
-Song?

07:59.890 --> 08:01.090
-Song?
-Little Song?

08:01.390 --> 08:01.820
Song?

08:02.190 --> 08:03.450
Was he here last night?

08:03.560 --> 08:04.180
Yes.

08:04.220 --> 08:05.070
This... this is the dinner

08:05.070 --> 08:06.730
I prepared for him last night.

08:09.250 --> 08:11.180
Might have gone out at midnight.

08:11.300 --> 08:12.890
Go check the hallway.

08:13.250 --> 08:14.560
Anyone got up last night?

08:14.560 --> 08:15.180
I didn't.

08:15.800 --> 08:16.680
Me neither.

08:20.270 --> 08:21.730
What about you, Xu Shengli?

08:21.730 --> 08:23.020
I went to the bathroom.

08:23.450 --> 08:24.450
It was him then.

08:26.600 --> 08:28.480
You came back after midnight, no?

08:29.450 --> 08:30.800
Okay, case solved.

08:31.370 --> 08:32.429
The squirrel

08:32.600 --> 08:33.549
got out of the cage

08:33.549 --> 08:34.750
by itself last night.

08:35.380 --> 08:37.000
Then the door

08:37.030 --> 08:38.090
opened and closed,

08:38.240 --> 08:39.460
and it went out to play.

08:39.460 --> 08:41.059
Let's go look in the hallway.

08:41.409 --> 08:42.669
Was it you, Xu Shengli?

08:43.100 --> 08:43.840
I'm talking to you!

08:43.840 --> 08:44.390
Was it you?

08:44.390 --> 08:45.000
What are you doing?

08:45.000 --> 08:46.720
-I'm sleeping. Can you guys talk later?
-Zongbao.

08:46.720 --> 08:47.550
Zongbao, you probably don't know,

08:47.550 --> 08:48.720
one day when neither of you were around,

08:48.720 --> 08:49.260
he...

08:49.340 --> 08:51.200
he said Little Song has germs

08:51.250 --> 08:52.370
and isn't sanitary.

08:52.370 --> 08:53.100
He's never liked

08:53.100 --> 08:54.010
my son!

08:54.170 --> 08:55.500
Can you guys talk later?

08:55.870 --> 08:56.280
Get up.

08:56.460 --> 08:56.950
No.

08:57.080 --> 08:57.810
I said get up!

08:57.870 --> 08:58.550
I won't!

08:58.670 --> 08:59.750
Get up now!

09:04.620 --> 09:06.150
Zongbao, it's Little Song!

09:08.250 --> 09:09.840
I knew it was you, Xu Shengli!

09:09.840 --> 09:10.460
Move!

09:17.890 --> 09:19.570
Those nightmares in 108—

09:19.600 --> 09:21.230
what are they up to now?

09:21.720 --> 09:23.320
Coming through. Move, move.

09:24.140 --> 09:25.410
Sounds like a homicide.

09:25.410 --> 09:26.340
Call the police.

09:26.600 --> 09:27.800
Don't talk nonsense.

09:29.630 --> 09:30.450
Open the door!

09:30.620 --> 09:32.770
It's me, Little Northeasterner.
Open the door!

09:32.770 --> 09:34.050
If someone really gets killed,

09:34.050 --> 09:36.050
we're not going to stay here anymore.

09:36.050 --> 09:37.250
I'm going to get the key.

09:37.250 --> 09:38.450
Officer Tang is here!

09:38.600 --> 09:40.170
Little Northeasterner!

09:40.220 --> 09:40.820
Mayday!

09:40.870 --> 09:42.100
Officer Tang is here!

09:45.510 --> 09:46.620
You guys are going to

09:46.620 --> 09:47.860
ruin my business!

09:48.340 --> 09:48.820
Can't you manage

09:48.820 --> 09:50.480
your little hostel properly?

09:50.840 --> 09:52.550
It's causing trouble every day!

09:52.550 --> 09:53.360
I come here eight times a week,

09:53.360 --> 09:53.890
you know?

09:56.150 --> 09:57.390
Right, right.

10:00.170 --> 10:03.260
[The memory lives on, the legacy endures,
forever with us]

10:00.410 --> 10:01.680
Xu Shengli.

10:02.600 --> 10:04.530
Have you been here a week yet?

10:05.200 --> 10:07.200
The police have come twice already.

10:08.030 --> 10:09.510
I really regret

10:09.510 --> 10:10.200
bringing you here

10:10.200 --> 10:11.760
from the train station.

10:12.770 --> 10:14.290
Whatever is going on in 108—

10:14.290 --> 10:15.370
just let me know today

10:15.370 --> 10:16.820
if you can sort it out.

10:17.000 --> 10:18.320
If this place is too small

10:18.320 --> 10:19.220
for a big shot like you,

10:19.220 --> 10:20.750
I won't try to keep you.

10:21.050 --> 10:22.580
For six yuan a day for the bed

10:22.630 --> 10:24.010
I get 600 yuan's worth of hassle.

10:24.010 --> 10:25.440
Can anyone stand this?

10:27.750 --> 10:29.010
Sorry for the trouble.

10:30.480 --> 10:31.480
I'm really sorry.

10:32.460 --> 10:33.990
I'll figure something out.

10:34.750 --> 10:35.860
My condolences.

10:36.510 --> 10:37.570
And another thing.

10:38.790 --> 10:41.480
It's not easy for anyone out here.

10:42.010 --> 10:43.810
Don't back people into a corner.

10:43.840 --> 10:45.370
Even a worm will turn!

11:00.910 --> 11:01.440
Zongbao,

11:03.840 --> 11:04.570
Liangliang,

11:06.630 --> 11:08.290
Little Song was just like you.

11:09.700 --> 11:11.360
You're all my closest family.

11:11.670 --> 11:12.820
He came to Beijing with me

11:12.820 --> 11:14.150
all the way from Shanxi.

11:14.650 --> 11:16.980
We traveled thousands of miles together.

11:17.630 --> 11:18.120
Okay.

11:18.460 --> 11:19.940
In so many lonely moments,

11:21.360 --> 11:22.490
he was there with me.

11:22.620 --> 11:25.450
[The memory lives on, the legacy endures,
forever with us]

11:23.270 --> 11:24.390
On so many cold nights,

11:24.390 --> 11:25.390
he warmed my heart

11:25.510 --> 11:26.670
with his warmth.

11:27.500 --> 11:28.900
In the scorching summer,

11:29.200 --> 11:30.300
its playfulness

11:30.330 --> 11:31.750
brought me true relief.

11:33.080 --> 11:33.540
Song...

11:35.480 --> 11:36.410
we were friends.

11:37.890 --> 11:39.130
We were father and son.

11:39.130 --> 11:41.900
[The memory lives on, the legacy endures,
forever with us]

11:39.380 --> 11:40.530
We were fellow sufferers

11:40.530 --> 11:41.240
and family.

11:41.980 --> 11:43.640
But since you've been with me,

11:44.120 --> 11:45.480
we've only shared hardships—

11:45.480 --> 11:47.290
we never got to share any good time.

11:47.290 --> 11:48.200
I haven't been able

11:48.200 --> 11:49.580
to give you a single day of happiness,

11:49.580 --> 11:51.200
and now... now you've been killed

11:51.200 --> 11:52.530
by a bad guy.

11:52.700 --> 11:54.360
-Okay. Okay.
-Here's my word—

11:54.440 --> 11:55.920
if I don't avenge you,

11:56.050 --> 11:57.160
I'm not a man.

11:57.200 --> 11:58.720
Okay, okay...

11:58.790 --> 12:00.630
My condolences.

12:00.670 --> 12:01.510
My condolences.

12:01.510 --> 12:02.520
My condolences.

12:02.840 --> 12:03.370
Cao Ye,

12:04.910 --> 12:06.240
I really didn't mean to.

12:07.030 --> 12:08.080
I really don't know

12:08.080 --> 12:09.340
when it got onto my bed.

12:09.580 --> 12:09.980
But...

12:11.120 --> 12:12.000
I did crush it.

12:13.340 --> 12:14.120
I apologize.

12:15.370 --> 12:15.900
Okay now.

12:18.390 --> 12:19.250
I'm someone who

12:19.650 --> 12:20.980
doesn't usually drink.

12:22.860 --> 12:25.000
Take this as my apology.

12:31.580 --> 12:32.960
What do you mean "take this as"?

12:32.960 --> 12:34.720
Even at a grave, you pour three cups.

12:34.720 --> 12:35.270
One cup?

12:35.340 --> 12:36.740
Who are you trying to impress?

12:36.740 --> 12:38.010
Is this how you Shandong people do things?

12:38.010 --> 12:39.030
Don't... Stop, stop.

12:39.030 --> 12:40.410
Why are you covering my mouth?

12:40.410 --> 12:41.140
Tell me then.

12:42.500 --> 12:43.600
What do I have to do

12:43.630 --> 12:44.390
to put this behind us?

12:44.390 --> 12:45.980
Listen, Xu Shengli.

12:46.170 --> 12:46.970
In this world,

12:47.010 --> 12:48.340
it's not like for everything that happens,

12:48.340 --> 12:49.240
you just say "sorry,"

12:49.240 --> 12:49.910
and I have to forgive you.

12:49.910 --> 12:50.460
Alright now.

12:50.460 --> 12:51.730
I don't accept your apology.

12:51.730 --> 12:52.730
I don't accept it!

12:52.790 --> 12:54.420
A life for a life.

12:54.460 --> 12:55.360
That was a life.

12:55.500 --> 12:55.980
A life!

12:55.980 --> 12:57.240
Okay, okay, okay.

12:58.700 --> 12:59.360
A life, yeah?

12:59.360 --> 13:00.290
My condolences.

13:03.610 --> 13:04.270
Why are you drinking—

13:04.270 --> 13:05.340
Let him drink.

13:06.700 --> 13:08.170
But... the liquor...

13:08.270 --> 13:09.240
He's finishing it!

13:09.240 --> 13:10.200
Leave it.

13:10.790 --> 13:12.010
Alright, alright, alright.

13:12.010 --> 13:13.580
Stop drinking. Stop drinking!

13:13.580 --> 13:14.710
Hey, stop drinking.

13:14.750 --> 13:16.150
You'll harm yourself...

13:16.820 --> 13:18.220
If this is not enough,
I'll go buy some more.

13:18.220 --> 13:18.960
No, no, don't.

13:18.960 --> 13:19.580
I'm laying my life down

13:19.580 --> 13:20.580
right here today.

13:20.630 --> 13:22.250
Enough with your drunken fit!

13:22.250 --> 13:22.870
You were asking

13:22.870 --> 13:23.740
how to put this behind us?

13:23.740 --> 13:25.100
Fine. I'll tell you, Xu Shengli.

13:25.100 --> 13:26.160
Bring Little Song

13:26.270 --> 13:27.670
back to me safe and sound,

13:27.670 --> 13:28.820
and I'll put this behind us.

13:28.820 --> 13:29.810
Can you do that?

13:29.870 --> 13:31.510
You can't!

13:33.000 --> 13:33.580
I know,

13:35.790 --> 13:37.660
you guys have a problem with me.

13:39.010 --> 13:40.850
You think I'm arrogant.

13:41.650 --> 13:42.340
I admit it.

13:43.980 --> 13:45.240
When I first came here,

13:45.670 --> 13:46.840
I was arrogant.

13:47.770 --> 13:48.700
But I have never

13:48.750 --> 13:50.550
looked down on anyone.

13:52.120 --> 13:53.500
We met by chance.

13:54.290 --> 13:56.290
Getting to live under the same roof

13:56.340 --> 13:57.840
is serendipity.

13:58.650 --> 14:00.590
Why can't we just

14:01.100 --> 14:03.540
live in peace...

14:04.320 --> 14:05.030
in peace...

14:09.010 --> 14:09.780
Shengli?

14:10.510 --> 14:11.080
Shengli?

14:12.050 --> 14:13.980
You're going to get yourself sick.

14:14.340 --> 14:16.210
You two are really something, aren't you?

14:16.210 --> 14:16.940
A Beijinger

14:17.010 --> 14:18.100
and a Shanxi guy

14:18.130 --> 14:19.770
got a Shandong guy this wasted.

14:19.770 --> 14:22.740
-Going to brag for the rest of your lives?
-He drank it himself.

14:22.740 --> 14:23.710
Xu Shengli.

14:24.600 --> 14:25.400
A call for you.

14:27.250 --> 14:28.180
What's going on?

14:30.510 --> 14:31.370
He drank

14:31.480 --> 14:32.740
half a bottle himself.

14:34.000 --> 14:34.820
Xu Shengli.

14:35.340 --> 14:36.080
A call for you.

14:36.080 --> 14:36.320
Shengli.

14:36.320 --> 14:37.450
It's Director Weng.

14:45.030 --> 14:45.490
What...

14:47.290 --> 14:48.530
What's going on now,

14:48.550 --> 14:49.460
my lords?

14:57.980 --> 14:58.580
Zhuang...

14:59.440 --> 15:00.580
Why are you here?

15:10.670 --> 15:12.670
Director Weng called me yesterday?

15:15.840 --> 15:16.340
No, no.

15:16.410 --> 15:16.870
What are you doing?

15:16.870 --> 15:18.130
I have to call him back.

15:18.250 --> 15:19.510
What are you doing? Sit down!

15:19.510 --> 15:21.370
Sit down. Are you out of your mind?

15:21.410 --> 15:22.870
You got yourself acute alcohol poisoning,

15:22.870 --> 15:23.670
are you aware?

15:24.240 --> 15:25.080
You had a fever over 40 degrees.

15:25.080 --> 15:26.810
Even your trachea got swollen.

15:34.130 --> 15:36.820
I still have to call him back...

15:37.390 --> 15:38.620
When you're back later today,

15:38.620 --> 15:40.750
can you call Director Weng back for me?

15:41.240 --> 15:42.320
Lie down first.

15:49.840 --> 15:50.570
Don't worry.

15:51.250 --> 15:53.250
I'll explain it to him when I'm back.

15:54.100 --> 15:55.410
But please don't tell him

15:55.410 --> 15:56.840
that I'm hospitalized because of drinking.

15:56.840 --> 15:58.100
Now you're scared?

15:59.250 --> 16:00.650
Why did you drink so much?

16:03.960 --> 16:04.910
Did the guys in 108

16:04.910 --> 16:05.670
force you to drink?

16:05.670 --> 16:06.170
No.

16:08.200 --> 16:09.860
It has nothing to do with them.

16:10.630 --> 16:12.430
Drinking so much when you can't.

16:13.010 --> 16:13.770
Reckless.

16:20.360 --> 16:21.690
I think we've taken this

16:22.770 --> 16:24.350
a bit too far.

16:24.620 --> 16:25.440
How so?

16:27.940 --> 16:29.120
Are you betraying us?

16:29.120 --> 16:29.860
No, no.

16:30.150 --> 16:32.140
It's just, after all this trouble,

16:32.390 --> 16:33.920
I'm feeling kind of guilty.

16:35.100 --> 16:35.630
Zongbao.

16:36.940 --> 16:37.550
Well,

16:38.340 --> 16:39.480
one thing led to another,

16:39.480 --> 16:40.610
and we ended up here.

16:41.250 --> 16:43.890
He's in the hospital now,

16:43.960 --> 16:44.490
isn't he?

16:45.000 --> 16:46.130
Saying this now...

16:47.270 --> 16:47.960
is too late.

16:48.630 --> 16:50.300
Maybe in the future,

16:50.500 --> 16:51.470
if there's any

16:51.600 --> 16:52.670
Tom, Dick, or Harry

16:52.740 --> 16:53.370
who joins us,

16:53.370 --> 16:54.500
we can give him some—

16:58.220 --> 16:59.220
You didn't knock.

16:59.500 --> 17:00.360
Is that polite?

17:00.440 --> 17:01.620
With unreasonable people,

17:01.620 --> 17:03.200
there's no need for politeness.

17:03.200 --> 17:04.730
Who's being unreasonable?

17:04.849 --> 17:05.960
Is it fun for you guys

17:05.960 --> 17:07.640
to bully people all the time?

17:07.980 --> 17:09.069
Do you have to drive people out

17:09.069 --> 17:10.109
for your own enjoyment?

17:10.109 --> 17:11.140
We're all from out of town.

17:11.140 --> 17:12.200
Is this necessary?

17:15.829 --> 17:17.140
He's very sick right now.

17:17.140 --> 17:17.640
You're all

17:17.640 --> 17:19.069
responsible for that.

17:19.220 --> 17:21.079
You should pay the medical bills.

17:21.310 --> 17:22.829
Discussing money is a bit too much.

17:22.829 --> 17:23.980
Well... my son, Little Song,

17:23.980 --> 17:25.460
was crushed to death by him.

17:25.460 --> 17:27.109
I didn't ask him for money.

17:27.180 --> 17:28.069
Who's responsible?

17:28.069 --> 17:29.030
Who's paying?

17:29.110 --> 17:30.640
He drank the liquor himself.

17:30.640 --> 17:31.770
Why should we pay

17:31.770 --> 17:32.590
half the medical bills?

17:32.590 --> 17:32.810
Right.

17:32.810 --> 17:33.550
Besides,

17:33.850 --> 17:34.750
he grinds his teeth, farts,

17:34.750 --> 17:35.700
smacks his lips,

17:35.700 --> 17:36.700
and talks in sleep.

17:36.700 --> 17:38.030
Who could stand all that?

17:38.030 --> 17:38.530
Exactly.

17:38.530 --> 17:39.310
If you can stand it,

17:39.310 --> 17:40.330
let him stay in your room.

17:40.330 --> 17:41.000
Tell me about it.

17:41.000 --> 17:41.740
So he...

17:41.810 --> 17:43.310
he just didn't sleep well for one night.

17:43.310 --> 17:44.290
He drank a bit and got like that.

17:44.290 --> 17:45.510
But what about us on a daily basis? Right?

17:45.510 --> 17:46.090
Exactly.

17:46.550 --> 17:48.350
Are you going to sort this or not?

17:53.500 --> 17:54.700
Are you going to sort this?

17:54.700 --> 17:55.420
Don't think just because

17:55.420 --> 17:56.070
you're a girl,

17:56.070 --> 17:57.110
you can yell at us

17:57.180 --> 17:57.770
and we have to

17:57.770 --> 17:58.420
indulge you

17:58.420 --> 17:58.900
and put up

17:58.900 --> 17:59.560
with you.

17:59.610 --> 18:00.520
A girl gets to

18:00.660 --> 18:01.270
blow up

18:01.420 --> 18:02.070
and kill?

18:02.270 --> 18:04.270
I'm curious to see, here in Beijing—

18:09.760 --> 18:10.290
What...

18:10.740 --> 18:11.830
What are you doing?

18:11.830 --> 18:12.330
Zhuang Zhuang!

18:12.330 --> 18:12.960
I... I...

18:13.030 --> 18:13.920
You planning to move out of here

18:13.920 --> 18:14.480
or what?

18:14.480 --> 18:16.050
Such a waste!

18:16.750 --> 18:17.610
Zhuang Zhuang.

18:18.290 --> 18:19.470
Stop walking.

18:19.530 --> 18:21.270
Messing with a young master of Beijing—

18:21.270 --> 18:22.610
you'll have nowhere to go in this city.

18:22.610 --> 18:23.610
I don't care if you have anywhere to go.

18:23.610 --> 18:24.570
You have to pay for that jar
of chili sauce.

18:24.570 --> 18:25.140
You...

18:33.240 --> 18:34.020
What now?

18:34.070 --> 18:34.800
What do we do?

18:35.700 --> 18:36.810
Let's go back and discuss.

18:36.810 --> 18:39.070
What are you doing? Why are you shouting?

18:39.160 --> 18:40.520
Why are you at our door?

18:44.010 --> 18:45.540
Isn't this Miss Celebrity?

18:45.550 --> 18:47.350
I was just about to report to you.

18:47.510 --> 18:48.870
Our wish

18:49.030 --> 18:50.230
is about to come true.

18:50.900 --> 18:52.310
What are you talking about?

18:52.310 --> 18:53.810
That annoying guy in our room

18:53.810 --> 18:55.670
is moving out soon.

18:56.380 --> 18:58.840
This one in your room
won't stay long either.

18:59.680 --> 19:00.870
She can't leave.

19:01.090 --> 19:02.130
She is my sister.

19:02.380 --> 19:03.950
If you two dare to bully my sister,

19:03.950 --> 19:04.740
you're dead.

19:04.850 --> 19:05.650
Wait, your...

19:05.850 --> 19:07.380
-Her sister?
-Your sister?

19:12.460 --> 19:14.290
How did she become her sister?

19:21.090 --> 19:22.330
You've fully recovered?

19:22.330 --> 19:24.250
My vitality is surging back.

19:24.290 --> 19:25.890
A registered parcel for you.

19:26.770 --> 19:27.700
Let it surge back slowly.

19:27.700 --> 19:28.250
Or just don't hold me

19:28.250 --> 19:29.780
responsible for anything.

19:34.790 --> 19:35.390
Sign here.

19:39.160 --> 19:40.960
I know nothing about scriptwriting,

19:40.960 --> 19:41.900
but looks like you're getting

19:41.900 --> 19:42.850
better and better at it.

19:42.850 --> 19:43.580
I mean, look,

19:43.610 --> 19:45.090
these letters with Capital Film Studio

19:45.090 --> 19:46.490
are going back and forth.

19:51.500 --> 19:52.350
Two cents for radishes.

19:52.350 --> 19:53.550
Get me a bunch a those.

19:56.850 --> 19:58.450
Why are you here again?

19:58.660 --> 19:59.740
Our backlog of scripts

19:59.740 --> 20:00.570
have all been sent back.

20:00.570 --> 20:01.970
Didn't you receive them?

20:02.090 --> 20:02.570
Mr. Wu,

20:03.420 --> 20:05.420
I'm not looking for Director Weng today.

20:05.420 --> 20:06.550
I'm looking for you.

20:06.810 --> 20:08.470
But why are you looking for me?

20:09.420 --> 20:10.680
I received the script.

20:12.570 --> 20:13.900
I just wanted to ask you,

20:14.010 --> 20:15.410
did you read this script?

20:16.920 --> 20:17.810
Isn't it obvious?

20:17.810 --> 20:19.740
Just tell me, did you read it or not?

20:21.500 --> 20:22.100
Look, I...

20:22.720 --> 20:24.160
Well... what do you want?

20:28.570 --> 20:29.630
Within the script,

20:30.180 --> 20:31.380
I glued three places.

20:32.510 --> 20:33.570
I don't assume you read it

20:33.570 --> 20:35.300
and glued them back, or did you?

20:37.070 --> 20:37.810
Mr. Wu,

20:38.570 --> 20:39.340
everyone,

20:40.010 --> 20:41.870
I really regard you as my seniors.

20:42.700 --> 20:43.380
I just hoped

20:43.420 --> 20:44.660
that you could give me some guidance

20:44.660 --> 20:45.460
and advice.

20:45.530 --> 20:46.460
That's all.

20:47.850 --> 20:48.570
I am just

20:48.610 --> 20:50.090
a young man with a dream.

20:50.940 --> 20:52.020
I so longed to meet

20:52.050 --> 20:53.320
mentors like you,

20:53.420 --> 20:55.110
seniors who could guide me.

20:55.350 --> 20:56.740
Like seeing a lighthouse in the dark,

20:56.740 --> 20:57.800
showing me the way.

20:57.900 --> 20:58.900
Are you not willing to shed

20:58.900 --> 20:59.980
even that little bit of light?

20:59.980 --> 21:01.690
What dream? What lighthouse?

21:01.810 --> 21:03.110
This is a studio.

21:03.900 --> 21:05.700
We have a heavy workload.

21:07.720 --> 21:08.200
Young man,

21:08.200 --> 21:09.530
I'll tell you the truth.

21:09.550 --> 21:10.830
Director Weng never asked us

21:10.830 --> 21:12.160
to read your script.

21:12.770 --> 21:13.830
Do you understand?

21:18.590 --> 21:19.640
If you want to wait,

21:19.640 --> 21:20.550
go ahead and wait.

21:20.550 --> 21:21.280
I don't mind.

21:21.440 --> 21:22.640
But don't wait in the office.

21:22.640 --> 21:23.550
We're all just trying

21:23.550 --> 21:24.480
to make a living.

21:24.590 --> 21:26.590
No one is here to play house with you.

21:33.100 --> 21:33.950
Young man,

21:34.270 --> 21:35.480
take the script back

21:35.510 --> 21:36.590
and polish it some more,

21:36.590 --> 21:37.830
and send it to us again.

21:37.830 --> 21:38.380
Trust me,

21:38.510 --> 21:40.040
we will definitely read it.

21:56.590 --> 21:57.450
Unbelievable.

22:24.640 --> 22:26.140
Reading it again?

22:26.790 --> 22:28.130
How many times have you

22:28.160 --> 22:29.820
read it now?

22:30.350 --> 22:31.370
You must know it by heart now.

22:31.370 --> 22:32.660
Fancy playing a role?

22:34.070 --> 22:35.000
I haven't finished it yet.

22:35.000 --> 22:35.730
I have to say,

22:36.500 --> 22:39.310
my son wrote a pretty interesting script.

22:39.880 --> 22:40.640
As I read it,

22:40.680 --> 22:41.850
I really got into it.

22:42.480 --> 22:44.110
I think you are interesting.

22:45.830 --> 22:46.560
-Why?
-Well,

22:46.680 --> 22:48.790
when he was home,

22:49.160 --> 22:50.270
you were always against him.

22:50.270 --> 22:50.920
Now he's gone,

22:50.920 --> 22:52.180
you tore up his script,

22:52.200 --> 22:54.660
and now you taped it
back together to read it.

22:54.720 --> 22:55.650
I mean, that's

22:55.720 --> 22:56.480
all in the past now,

22:56.480 --> 22:57.810
can't you just let it go?

22:58.070 --> 22:59.320
I tore it up, yes,

22:59.350 --> 23:00.550
but now I've taped it back together,

23:00.550 --> 23:01.000
okay?

23:02.070 --> 23:03.640
Am I not allowed to make mistakes?

23:03.640 --> 23:04.350
Fine, fine.

23:04.720 --> 23:05.270
Okay.

23:06.720 --> 23:07.780
What are you doing?

23:07.920 --> 23:08.880
I'm selling these books.

23:08.880 --> 23:10.690
You... you can't sell these.

23:10.720 --> 23:11.850
These are all his things.

23:11.850 --> 23:12.480
If he comes back and can't find them,

23:12.480 --> 23:13.590
he'll be upset.

23:13.680 --> 23:14.720
Is he coming back?

23:14.830 --> 23:16.290
Why wouldn't he come back?

23:16.900 --> 23:17.900
Where else would he go?

23:17.900 --> 23:19.680
Didn't you drive him away?

23:19.790 --> 23:20.510
So what?

23:21.070 --> 23:22.420
You're going to drive me away too,

23:22.420 --> 23:23.060
and be...

23:23.160 --> 23:24.720
and be the only one left in this house?

23:24.720 --> 23:26.030
I'm not trying to drive you away.

23:26.030 --> 23:26.960
I'm just saying,

23:27.250 --> 23:28.580
all these books in here,

23:28.680 --> 23:30.880
you bought him every single one of them.

23:31.270 --> 23:32.960
Throughout middle school and high school,

23:32.960 --> 23:34.330
you bought him whatever he wanted.

23:34.330 --> 23:35.350
Now he's grown up

23:35.400 --> 23:36.400
and wants to write scripts,

23:36.400 --> 23:37.150
you tell him,

23:37.400 --> 23:39.300
writing doesn't pay the bills.

23:39.350 --> 23:40.880
You even tore up his script.

23:41.150 --> 23:42.000
Now he's gone to Beijing,

23:42.000 --> 23:43.400
and you're suddenly reading the script.

23:43.400 --> 23:46.000
Aren't you saying one thing
but doing another?

23:46.160 --> 23:47.000
I tore it up, yes.

23:47.000 --> 23:48.550
But I've taped it back together, no?

23:48.550 --> 23:49.800
I've fixed it. Okay?

23:50.070 --> 23:50.510
Okay, okay.

23:50.510 --> 23:52.430
You just won't let this go.

23:52.640 --> 23:52.970
Fine.

23:53.000 --> 23:53.310
Alright, alright.

23:53.310 --> 23:55.220
Stop... stop this.

23:56.160 --> 23:57.370
Let's just eat, okay?

23:57.510 --> 23:59.110
I've got it all ready for you.

24:00.310 --> 24:01.610
Going to Beijing...

24:01.750 --> 24:03.610
It's not that I don't support him.

24:04.790 --> 24:06.650
But what kind of place is Beijing?

24:06.720 --> 24:08.380
It's full of talented people.

24:08.720 --> 24:10.250
I'm just worried about him.

24:12.920 --> 24:14.880
I'm worried he'll face rejection there.

24:14.880 --> 24:15.540
So,

24:16.400 --> 24:18.330
I'd rather he curse me in his heart,

24:19.200 --> 24:20.690
than have him suffer.

24:24.070 --> 24:25.000
No parent

24:25.030 --> 24:27.090
would not want their child to do well.

24:29.880 --> 24:30.410
Alright.

24:33.060 --> 24:34.260
I'll go get your food.

25:03.550 --> 25:05.150
Can I help you with anything?

25:05.830 --> 25:06.310
No need.

25:07.000 --> 25:07.750
Don't be mad.

25:07.790 --> 25:09.030
What are you mad about?

25:09.030 --> 25:09.770
Honestly.

25:18.010 --> 25:19.740
You keep the light on all night.

25:19.850 --> 25:20.610
Trying to keep us all up

25:20.610 --> 25:21.700
until we drop?

25:22.660 --> 25:24.180
It's just a light.

25:24.180 --> 25:25.090
I'll adjust it for you,

25:25.090 --> 25:25.660
okay?

25:25.660 --> 25:26.610
What good

25:26.660 --> 25:27.720
is all the whining?

25:28.980 --> 25:30.180
Seriously? Isn't that selfish?

25:30.180 --> 25:30.810
That's how you do it?

25:30.810 --> 25:31.220
How is Zongbao

25:31.220 --> 25:32.330
supposed to sleep?

25:32.980 --> 25:34.710
You should adjust it like this.

25:36.220 --> 25:36.790
You like the light so much?

25:36.790 --> 25:37.740
Can't live without it, yeah?

25:37.740 --> 25:38.660
Then shine it on yourself.

25:38.660 --> 25:40.120
Right on your face. There.

25:42.220 --> 25:43.530
Hey, what are you doing?

25:43.530 --> 25:45.350
The light's gone, noise is on?

25:45.530 --> 25:46.510
Shut your mouth.

25:46.570 --> 25:48.090
-Are you done?
-Is the noise my fault?

25:48.090 --> 25:49.050
Listen!

25:52.290 --> 25:52.960
I quit my secure job

25:52.960 --> 25:54.110
at the state factory

25:54.180 --> 25:55.760
to come to Beijing.

25:56.740 --> 25:57.540
Director Weng

25:58.270 --> 25:59.570
is my lifeline.

25:59.900 --> 26:01.470
I missed his call.

26:01.660 --> 26:02.650
That is my fate.

26:03.140 --> 26:04.740
If I can't see Director Weng,

26:04.740 --> 26:05.450
I won't know

26:05.470 --> 26:06.330
what to do next.

26:06.740 --> 26:08.180
But I have to stay in Beijing.

26:08.180 --> 26:09.580
I have to support myself.

26:09.740 --> 26:11.420
So I sell clothes during the day,

26:11.420 --> 26:13.000
and I write at night.

26:13.640 --> 26:15.240
Whether you can put up with me

26:15.570 --> 26:16.570
is your business.

26:17.460 --> 26:18.770
And I don't know how you guys

26:18.770 --> 26:19.810
make a living.

26:19.980 --> 26:20.980
But let me ask you—

26:21.330 --> 26:21.940
if someone

26:21.940 --> 26:23.670
tries to ruin your livelihood—

26:24.570 --> 26:26.300
tries to ruin your livelihood,

26:28.980 --> 26:30.840
would you fight them to the death?

26:50.200 --> 26:51.810
Honestly, you two.

26:53.680 --> 26:55.200
Everyone has a place in their heart

26:55.200 --> 26:56.040
that is

26:56.070 --> 26:57.720
more important than their life.

26:57.720 --> 26:59.440
You can't touch that.

26:59.720 --> 27:01.880
You two know that better than anyone.

27:03.140 --> 27:03.920
All of us

27:04.400 --> 27:05.160
left home

27:05.200 --> 27:06.350
on our own.

27:08.330 --> 27:09.460
It hasn't been easy.

27:09.880 --> 27:10.310
Right?

27:24.830 --> 27:26.570
This kid is a good kid.

27:26.660 --> 27:28.310
Look how angry he was just now.

27:28.310 --> 27:30.060
But he didn't touch your sax.

27:30.790 --> 27:32.520
He didn't touch your painting.

27:33.530 --> 27:35.400
Let's just let it go.

27:36.510 --> 27:37.050
Okay?

28:19.480 --> 28:21.650
Screenwriter Xu, that speech just now

28:22.850 --> 28:24.640
was quite impassioned.

28:25.880 --> 28:26.720
I'm sorry.

28:26.920 --> 28:28.450
I got a little carried away.

28:28.640 --> 28:30.100
You should be passionate.

28:30.110 --> 28:32.110
How can you create without passion?

28:37.360 --> 28:37.800
Right.

28:42.160 --> 28:43.750
Why are you still up?

28:44.070 --> 28:45.270
I came up for a stroll.

28:56.050 --> 28:57.650
If it's too noisy down there,

28:57.680 --> 28:59.110
I think this place is nice.

28:59.110 --> 29:00.030
It's quiet.

29:01.290 --> 29:02.950
Perfect for writing scripts.

29:07.060 --> 29:07.580
Yes...

29:08.310 --> 29:08.640
Here.

29:10.090 --> 29:10.510
Try it.

29:13.050 --> 29:13.510
This...

29:17.330 --> 29:17.880
I...

29:20.830 --> 29:21.890
Does it feel right?

29:22.280 --> 29:23.410
This... this works.

29:24.290 --> 29:25.130
Work hard.

29:25.480 --> 29:26.880
Make a name for yourself.

29:27.030 --> 29:28.690
Show everyone what you can do.

29:32.750 --> 29:33.430
Very nice.

29:34.110 --> 29:35.770
You look like a model student.

29:37.000 --> 29:37.950
Work hard.

29:38.110 --> 29:39.410
Get famous soon,

29:39.640 --> 29:40.790
and pay me back.

29:43.510 --> 29:44.000
Okay.

29:44.860 --> 29:45.920
Goodbye, Teacher.

29:59.950 --> 30:03.720
[Yingkelai Beijing-Style Cuisine]

30:20.800 --> 30:21.500
Honey,

30:22.020 --> 30:23.220
get some spiced beef.

30:25.990 --> 30:29.380
[Food Pickup]

30:26.960 --> 30:27.560
Hello,

30:27.640 --> 30:29.920
two bowls of porridge and
four fried dough sticks.

30:29.920 --> 30:31.680
[Beijing-Style Homemade Dishes]

30:30.270 --> 30:31.140
Let's sit here.

30:31.760 --> 30:35.600
[Food Pickup]

30:32.850 --> 30:34.700
Hello, a bowl of soy milk

30:34.830 --> 30:36.360
and two fried dough sticks.

30:42.520 --> 30:46.580
[Yingkelai Beijing-Style Cuisine]

31:17.470 --> 31:19.400
[Yingkelai Beijing-Style Cuisine]

31:17.680 --> 31:19.140
Throughout Russia,

31:19.330 --> 31:20.850
over half of all the "Bulajis"

31:20.850 --> 31:22.060
were imported by me.

31:22.590 --> 31:24.450
You don't know what a "Bulaji" is?

31:24.570 --> 31:26.330
A "Bulaji" is a dress.

31:27.900 --> 31:29.190
The dresses... You...

31:28.920 --> 31:30.040
[Honest Owner That Returns Lost Items]

31:29.500 --> 31:30.200
Listen,

31:30.240 --> 31:31.160
I make tens of thousands a day.

31:31.160 --> 31:32.610
Would I default on that little bit?

31:32.610 --> 31:33.500
I'm still answering your call,

31:33.500 --> 31:34.560
I'm still here.

31:35.050 --> 31:36.720
Hello? I can't hear you. Hello?

31:36.720 --> 31:37.220
Hello?

31:38.200 --> 31:39.800
I can't hear you. Talk later.

31:40.200 --> 31:41.600
Hounding me all day long.

31:41.960 --> 31:42.960
What can I get you?

31:44.660 --> 31:45.220
Mr. Tao,

31:45.250 --> 31:46.580
don't you recognize me?

31:47.270 --> 31:48.020
Jun?

31:48.380 --> 31:49.920
You changed your hairstyle.

31:49.920 --> 31:51.250
Wasn't it slicked back?

31:51.270 --> 31:52.800
I'll get a perm afterwards.

31:53.140 --> 31:54.500
Where's your own son, Liangliang?

31:54.500 --> 31:55.290
That little brat.

31:55.290 --> 31:56.310
I don't know where he went.

31:56.310 --> 31:57.460
Probably went to do art.

31:57.460 --> 31:58.970
As long as he's alive.

31:59.330 --> 32:00.940
He doesn't come here as often as you do.

32:00.940 --> 32:02.510
I'm visiting you on his behalf.

32:02.510 --> 32:03.380
What can I get you?

32:03.380 --> 32:04.050
The usual.

32:04.160 --> 32:05.070
About 150 grams of beef.

32:05.070 --> 32:06.870
And noodles with soybean paste.

32:08.970 --> 32:10.970
I don't have change. Only hundreds.

32:12.090 --> 32:12.950
Next time then.

32:14.510 --> 32:15.120
Generous.

32:15.710 --> 32:17.310
Don't be shy to ask next time.

32:17.880 --> 32:18.810
A bottle of soda.

32:19.250 --> 32:20.770
You sure can eat and drink.

32:40.250 --> 32:41.240
I'm off, Mr. Tao.

32:41.790 --> 32:42.990
Money is on the table.

32:49.940 --> 32:51.340
Check this out. How is it?

32:52.960 --> 32:53.640
Why are you

32:53.680 --> 32:54.960
wearing a raincoat on a sunny day?

32:54.960 --> 32:56.500
I'm wearing a raincoat on the outside,

32:56.500 --> 32:58.000
and a short-sleeved shirt inside.

32:58.000 --> 32:59.270
I'm trying to display our clothes

32:59.270 --> 33:00.520
as much as possible.

33:00.680 --> 33:02.210
Don't be silly. Take it off.

33:02.380 --> 33:03.070
Aren't you hot?

33:03.070 --> 33:03.900
Not at all.

33:04.070 --> 33:04.480
Look.

33:05.530 --> 33:06.380
I'm not hot.

33:06.720 --> 33:07.960
Funny dude, huh?

33:08.250 --> 33:09.650
Don't mind him.

33:09.940 --> 33:10.830
Take a look at the clothes.

33:10.830 --> 33:11.420
I like this one.

33:11.420 --> 33:12.580
Check this out!

33:12.920 --> 33:13.550
Don't miss out!

33:13.550 --> 33:14.920
Come visit again.

33:15.100 --> 33:15.500
Okay.

33:15.510 --> 33:16.320
-Sure.
-Here.

33:16.750 --> 33:17.240
Thank you.

33:17.240 --> 33:17.840
Thank you.

33:23.570 --> 33:24.480
Are you hot?

33:24.920 --> 33:25.330
No.

33:25.960 --> 33:27.740
Take it off. You'll get heatstroke.

33:27.740 --> 33:28.800
No, no. I'm not hot.

33:28.980 --> 33:30.040
Is there any water?

33:30.090 --> 33:30.820
Water?

33:30.980 --> 33:31.980
I want some water.

33:35.070 --> 33:36.400
Did we finish our water?

33:37.200 --> 33:37.720
No water left?

33:37.720 --> 33:39.420
-Forget it. It's fine.
-Let me buy you a bottle.

33:39.420 --> 33:39.940
It's fine.

33:39.940 --> 33:41.000
Really, it's fine.

33:41.110 --> 33:42.010
You look like you've been poisoned.

33:42.010 --> 33:44.670
-There will be water later.
-Put away the money.

33:59.460 --> 34:00.260
It's raining.

34:00.700 --> 34:01.550
It's raining!

34:09.500 --> 34:10.110
Boss.

34:10.320 --> 34:11.320
Here, put this on.

34:13.760 --> 34:15.290
Hurry, hurry. The clothes.

34:15.320 --> 34:15.670
Okay.

34:20.730 --> 34:21.090
Done.

34:23.110 --> 34:24.480
I'll show you a magic trick.

34:24.480 --> 34:25.340
Watch closely.

34:29.440 --> 34:29.900
Come on.

34:30.750 --> 34:32.310
Raincoats!

34:32.550 --> 34:34.159
No extra charge in the rain!

34:34.260 --> 34:35.070
Over here!

34:35.150 --> 34:35.630
Over here!

34:35.630 --> 34:36.150
Come on!

34:36.800 --> 34:37.840
Raincoats!

34:37.880 --> 34:39.360
No extra charge in the rain!

34:39.360 --> 34:40.159
One for me.

34:40.400 --> 34:41.620
All kinds of styles

34:41.820 --> 34:43.139
and colors!

34:45.130 --> 34:45.820
One for me.

34:45.820 --> 34:47.280
Five yuan. Five yuan each.

34:47.980 --> 34:48.560
Here.

34:48.780 --> 34:49.389
Over here.

34:49.610 --> 34:50.210
Five yuan.

34:51.170 --> 34:52.090
Okay, thank you.

34:52.090 --> 34:52.719
Thank you.

34:52.900 --> 34:53.280
Here.

34:54.010 --> 34:55.300
Come buy raincoats!

34:55.420 --> 34:55.940
Come on!

34:55.940 --> 34:56.710
Xu.

35:03.440 --> 35:04.070
It's wet.

35:05.920 --> 35:07.560
Pack our stuff up, quick.

35:07.650 --> 35:08.610
Pack all these clothes up.

35:08.610 --> 35:09.840
Pack them up. Put them inside.

35:09.840 --> 35:10.170
Here.

35:19.650 --> 35:20.940
Xu.

35:21.010 --> 35:21.720
You two

35:21.980 --> 35:23.180
really came out on top

35:23.300 --> 35:24.430
on the street today.

35:24.780 --> 35:25.980
How much did you make?

35:26.650 --> 35:28.320
I haven't finished calculating yet.

35:28.320 --> 35:29.090
Tell me now,

35:29.170 --> 35:31.030
how did you come up with this idea?

35:32.050 --> 35:33.170
It was a gift from above.

35:33.170 --> 35:35.090
Playing mysterious with me? Seriously.

35:35.090 --> 35:35.750
Spit it out.

35:36.320 --> 35:38.000
The weather forecast.

35:38.460 --> 35:39.530
I checked the weather forecast.

35:39.530 --> 35:40.530
It said it's going to rain

35:40.530 --> 35:41.530
for the next few days.

35:41.530 --> 35:42.650
I remembered no one sold raincoats

35:42.650 --> 35:43.610
in this market.

35:43.860 --> 35:45.720
So I decided to stock some and try.

35:45.820 --> 35:47.550
Aren't you clever. Seriously.

35:48.170 --> 35:49.010
You made money.

35:49.010 --> 35:49.820
Shouldn't you treat me

35:49.820 --> 35:50.420
to a drink?

35:50.530 --> 35:51.130
Of course.

35:51.380 --> 35:52.300
I want something ice-cold.

35:52.300 --> 35:52.630
Okay.

35:52.730 --> 35:53.130
Great.

35:53.170 --> 35:53.940
Get one for Zhuang Zhuang too.

35:53.940 --> 35:54.710
For sure.

36:01.210 --> 36:01.780
Tell me.

36:03.170 --> 36:04.970
What's going on between you two?

36:05.650 --> 36:07.050
We're business partners.

36:07.050 --> 36:09.900
Business partners? Who are you kidding?

36:10.170 --> 36:11.050
It's true.

36:11.420 --> 36:12.630
I saw you two just now,

36:13.300 --> 36:14.690
working in the rain like that.

36:14.690 --> 36:15.260
My mind,

36:15.340 --> 36:16.280
whoosh, went straight back

36:16.280 --> 36:17.400
to when I was young.

36:18.590 --> 36:19.530
Speaking of back then,

36:19.530 --> 36:21.050
I had so many guys chasing me too.

36:21.050 --> 36:22.260
That was awesome.

36:22.840 --> 36:23.750
Really?

36:24.280 --> 36:25.460
Of course.

36:25.550 --> 36:26.950
Go on and tell me about it.

36:27.570 --> 36:29.360
Anyway, good men are scarce.

36:29.460 --> 36:30.380
Grab him when you see one.

36:30.380 --> 36:31.500
The next one might not be as good.

36:31.500 --> 36:31.830
Here.

36:31.900 --> 36:33.420
-You're so beautiful.
-It's chilled.

36:33.420 --> 36:35.670
Open your eyes wide and take a good look.

36:35.800 --> 36:36.860
What are you talking about?

36:36.860 --> 36:38.020
I'm saying you have big eyes.

36:38.020 --> 36:39.080
My eyes aren't big.

36:39.090 --> 36:40.330
Your eyes are.

36:40.420 --> 36:40.950
I know.

36:40.980 --> 36:42.510
That's why I was so popular.

36:51.170 --> 36:53.030
Look at him, obsessed with money.

36:58.610 --> 37:00.140
Finished calculating yet?

37:02.730 --> 37:04.300
We made 250.

37:05.650 --> 37:06.500
That much?

37:06.650 --> 37:07.650
It suits you well.

37:14.320 --> 37:14.900
Boss,

37:15.570 --> 37:17.000
Little Northeasterner snatched
a lot of customers

37:17.000 --> 37:18.860
at the train station again today.

37:19.030 --> 37:20.480
The owners of the other hostels

37:20.480 --> 37:21.840
have begged me several times.

37:21.840 --> 37:23.130
They want to buy you dinner

37:23.130 --> 37:23.920
and discuss how to deal with

37:23.920 --> 37:25.550
this Little Northeasterner.

37:25.550 --> 37:27.590
Do I look like I'm starving?

37:28.230 --> 37:29.380
They buy me a meal,

37:29.400 --> 37:30.860
and I'll do their bidding?

37:31.610 --> 37:32.670
Understood, Boss.

37:33.090 --> 37:34.120
I'll go press them

37:34.280 --> 37:35.030
and see

37:35.190 --> 37:36.820
just how sincere they really are.

37:36.820 --> 37:37.710
Tell them,

37:38.480 --> 37:40.550
we are out here to make money.

37:42.480 --> 37:45.080
The greater the sincerity,
the bigger the job.

37:45.710 --> 37:47.240
If they are sincere enough,

37:47.590 --> 37:48.860
I can uproot Seasons Change

37:48.860 --> 37:49.970
entirely.

37:51.000 --> 37:51.530
Let's go.

37:51.650 --> 37:52.580
Take care, Boss.

38:02.780 --> 38:04.380
Listen up!

38:05.360 --> 38:06.570
You all look like decent people

38:06.570 --> 38:07.500
on the surface.

38:07.500 --> 38:08.210
He's starting again.

38:08.210 --> 38:08.830
But you act

38:08.860 --> 38:10.130
with no manners!

38:10.420 --> 38:12.020
Throwing trash everywhere.

38:12.030 --> 38:12.610
You just don't

38:12.610 --> 38:14.170
treat this place like your own home.

38:14.170 --> 38:14.940
If you piss me off,

38:14.940 --> 38:16.170
I'll kick you all out

38:16.530 --> 38:17.860
to sleep on the streets.

38:18.730 --> 38:20.300
Calm down.

38:20.340 --> 38:21.740
It's bad for your health.

38:28.230 --> 38:29.490
You two went out to eat?

38:30.980 --> 38:32.090
Didn't I tell you?

38:33.010 --> 38:34.260
You need to be careful.

38:34.260 --> 38:35.870
People will get jealous.

38:35.960 --> 38:36.890
Jealous of what?

38:37.130 --> 38:38.340
We made money from doing business.

38:38.340 --> 38:39.690
Can't we celebrate?

38:40.800 --> 38:42.090
I even brought you a dish.

38:42.090 --> 38:43.420
Forget it. I'll have it.

38:46.420 --> 38:48.350
I was saying that for your own good.

38:49.610 --> 38:50.810
Those people inside,

38:51.210 --> 38:52.340
looking all shifty,

38:53.090 --> 38:54.160
are all tough nuts.

38:54.260 --> 38:55.760
If I don't scold them every few days,

38:55.760 --> 38:57.760
they'll turn the place upside down.

38:58.940 --> 38:59.460
Mr. Xu,

39:00.570 --> 39:02.230
I see you've fully recovered.

39:02.860 --> 39:03.610
Don't take it to heart.

39:03.610 --> 39:05.010
Don't lower yourself to their level.

39:05.010 --> 39:05.870
How about this—

39:06.340 --> 39:07.090
I'll switch you to a different room.

39:07.090 --> 39:07.730
No need.

39:08.730 --> 39:09.940
I'm digging my heels in.

39:09.940 --> 39:10.870
I'm staying put.

39:15.210 --> 39:16.610
I'm staying in that room.

39:17.420 --> 39:18.200
Are you sure?

39:18.820 --> 39:19.280
Well...

39:20.510 --> 39:21.560
Mr. Xu,

39:21.880 --> 39:23.940
just let me know if you need anything.

39:30.550 --> 39:31.340
This liquor,

39:32.420 --> 39:33.420
and these dishes—

39:34.280 --> 39:35.510
as Xu said,

39:35.820 --> 39:38.230
he got these specially for us.

39:41.460 --> 39:42.010
Here.

39:44.570 --> 39:45.630
It's not poisoned.

39:47.300 --> 39:48.230
Did you have any?

39:50.090 --> 39:50.820
I had a bite

39:51.610 --> 39:52.680
of everything.

39:53.420 --> 39:54.420
Just a small bite.

39:57.420 --> 39:59.170
He's being too nice for no reason.

39:59.170 --> 40:00.500
He must be up to no good.

40:00.650 --> 40:02.170
What are you talking about?

40:02.170 --> 40:04.460
This is good food.

40:04.650 --> 40:06.260
It's already been reheated once.

40:06.260 --> 40:07.660
If we don't eat it now,

40:07.780 --> 40:09.780
it won't taste good reheated again.

40:10.340 --> 40:11.130
"Hoeing millet in the midday sun,

40:11.130 --> 40:12.460
every grain is hard work."

40:12.460 --> 40:13.660
If we throw this away,

40:13.690 --> 40:14.940
it would be a real pity.

40:14.940 --> 40:16.090
Corruption and waste

40:16.090 --> 40:17.530
are the biggest crimes.

40:18.400 --> 40:18.860
Come on.

40:24.420 --> 40:25.750
If you put it that way...

40:25.940 --> 40:26.340
No.

40:26.850 --> 40:27.930
What I mean is,

40:29.300 --> 40:30.030
Zongbao

40:30.170 --> 40:32.050
has already had a bite of everything.

40:32.050 --> 40:33.160
We can't let him be
the only one compromised,

40:33.160 --> 40:33.800
right?

40:34.420 --> 40:35.720
If he eats and we don't,

40:35.820 --> 40:37.310
it makes us look disloyal.

40:37.530 --> 40:39.230
So you mean

40:39.790 --> 40:41.450
we should share the blessings

40:41.650 --> 40:42.760
and the burden?

40:44.890 --> 40:46.050
Just eat.

40:48.380 --> 40:49.180
Wait a second.

40:49.610 --> 40:49.980
What?

40:51.530 --> 40:52.620
Just like Zongbao,

40:53.170 --> 40:54.970
we'll only take one bite of each.

40:55.530 --> 40:55.860
Okay.

41:02.420 --> 41:04.560
That bite is way too big.

41:04.860 --> 41:06.920
It counts as a bite if I can stuff it in.

41:07.130 --> 41:08.400
Don't waste it.

41:08.460 --> 41:09.520
You're wasting it.

41:16.690 --> 41:17.440
Oh my god.

41:20.830 --> 41:21.170
You...

41:21.170 --> 41:22.900
Why are you eating so much, too?

41:22.900 --> 41:24.410
This is your second round.

41:24.610 --> 41:25.860
That was just a taste test.

41:25.860 --> 41:27.120
Now I'm really eating.

41:30.500 --> 41:31.660
You two got

41:31.690 --> 41:32.130
all the slices.

41:32.130 --> 41:33.690
I'm only left with crumbs.

41:48.700 --> 41:49.570
It's tasty.

41:50.820 --> 41:51.350
Drink up.

41:51.860 --> 41:52.330
Come on.

42:01.570 --> 42:02.360
Cheers.

42:04.010 --> 42:04.670
Don't move!

42:19.360 --> 42:20.540
Is he delirious?

42:20.630 --> 42:21.570
Or is he awake?

42:24.480 --> 42:25.610
He's keeping score.

42:32.800 --> 42:33.600
You're awake?

42:37.260 --> 42:38.320
Then the three of us

42:39.210 --> 42:40.740
should get some more sleep.

42:43.270 --> 42:45.140
I'll go drain my bladder first.

42:52.840 --> 42:53.500
Is it good?
